race.comment: BERRY BLAST (13) resumed here in solid order and then raced on speed at Belmont beaten 1.4L over 1400m. Has a wide gate but Pike is a key jockey switch replacing the 3kg apprentice. Sits on the limit and up to the mile shouldn't bother. With average luck she'll be hard to beat. INVINCIBLE THIEF (5) was beaten a whisker here first-up over a mile and hasn't missed a beat. Has been tried twice at Stakes level and placed two back this trip at Ascot. The gate is awkward but stripping fitter she should be right in it.  BELLONA GIRL (9) spiked her figures placing here over this trip three weeks ago. Peaks now and has to be included. LATORIO (10) just missed heavily bet at York. This is harder but she will be fitter again and will be around the mark.
